📂 Datasets

This project uses multiple publicly available EEG datasets covering different neurological conditions. All datasets are used in their original form and processed through a unified preprocessing pipeline (filtering, ICA cleaning, channel selection, and epoching).

CHB-MIT Scalp EEG Database

https://physionet.org/content/chbmit/1.0.0/

The CHB-MIT dataset contains scalp EEG recordings from 23 pediatric patients with epilepsy (5 males aged 3–22 years and 17 females aged 1.5–19 years; one subject has two recording periods considered as separate cases, and one subject has missing demographic information). The recordings were acquired during long-term monitoring for epilepsy surgery evaluation, including medication withdrawal.

The EEG signals are sampled at 256 Hz using the international 10–20 electrode placement system. Most recordings are organized into approximately 1-hour sessions. The dataset primarily uses longitudinal bipolar montage configurations, although the recording device is not explicitly documented.

Schizophrenia EEG Dataset (IBIB PAN)

https://repod.icm.edu.pl/dataset.xhtml?persistentId=doi:10.18150/repod.0107441

This dataset contains EEG recordings from patients diagnosed with schizophrenia and healthy controls. It is used for classification and biomarker detection studies in psychiatric disorders.
The recordings are standard EEG acquisitions using clinical electrode setups, with sampling parameters and channel configurations defined by the original study protocol.

Dementia / Alzheimer’s EEG Dataset (AHEPA General Hospital of Thessaloniki)

https://openneuro.org/datasets/ds004504

This dataset includes EEG recordings from patients diagnosed with dementia and Alzheimer’s disease, collected in clinical hospital conditions. It contains multi-channel scalp EEG recordings acquired using standard clinical EEG systems.
Sampling frequency and channel configuration follow the clinical acquisition protocol described in the dataset documentation.

Autism Spectrum Disorder EEG Dataset (University of Sheffield)

https://orda.shef.ac.uk/articles/dataset/EEG_Data_for_Electrophysiological_signatures_of_brain_aging_in_autism_spectrum_disorder_/16840351

This dataset contains EEG recordings from individuals with autism spectrum disorder (ASD) and control subjects. It was designed to study electrophysiological signatures related to brain development and aging in ASD.

The recordings are multi-channel scalp EEG signals acquired using standard EEG recording systems. Details such as sampling rate, electrode montage, and session structure follow the original experimental protocol provided by the University of Sheffield dataset documentation.
